    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>By Mr. DUNCAN of South Carolina:H.R. 1637.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Because this legislation adjusts the formula the federalgovernment uses to spend money on federal contracts, it isauthorized by the Constitution under Article 1, Section 8,Clause 1, which grants Congress its spending power.[Page H2160]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
